snippet: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo, who defeated Rob Astorino, enters his second term without the aura of invincibility that aided him among Albany lawmakers.
abstract: New York Gov Andrew M Cuomo easily wins re-election, defeating conservative Westchester County Executive Rob Astorino; Cuomo's victory comes despite mixed feelings on part of voters and he enters his second term with less political clout than when campaign began, and with an uncertain future.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Al Baker, Susanne Craig, Tatiana Schlossberg, Nate Schweber and Nikita Stewart.

lead_paragraph: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo, who defeated Rob Astorino, enters his second term without the aura of invincibility that aided him among Albany lawmakers.

headline.main: Andrew Cuomo Is Re-elected New York Governor, but Loses Clout
headline.print_headline: Cuomo Secures a Second Term, but Loses Clout
